{"id":24893,"date":"2017-05-29T11:52:43","date_gmt":"2017-05-29T07:52:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=24893"},"modified":"2019-05-23T10:09:12","modified_gmt":"2019-05-23T06:09:12","slug":"quds-salat-masjid-aqsa","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/05\/29\/quds-salat-masjid-aqsa\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Jerusalem: Sins forgiven by praying at Masjid al-Aqsa"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>When Solomon, son of David, peace and blessings be upon him, built the Sacred House, he asked Allah Almighty for the three things throughout. Solomon asked Allah Almighty for judgment coinciding with His judgment, and he was given it. Solomon asked Allah Almighty for a kingdom none would have after him, and he was given it. And Solomon asked Allah Almighty when he finished the foundations of the Mosque that none would come to it, intending only to pray, but that his sins would be expunged like the day he was born from his mother<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Nasa\u0304&#8217;i\u0304 693<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u064d\u0648 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e <strong>\u0633\u064f\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u062f\u064e\u0627\u0648\u064f\u062f\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u065